The paper discusses the challenges and pitfalls of AI for social good and ethical considerations in AI design, which are relevant to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), cybernetics (cs.CY), emerging technologies (cs.ET), computer ethics (cs.CE), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, since the focus is on AI and ethics, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.CY and cs.ET, which also deal with ethical and social implications of technology. The other two sub-categories, cs.CE and cs.CR, are less likely but still relevant due to the discussion of ethical considerations and potential security issues in AI design.
